            <div class="hide" ><img onerror='imgError(this);' class="img-responsive m-b-10" src="<?=Assets?>images/help/help_base2.jpg" alt="Label Designer"></div>
            <div class="scrollbar" id="style-1">
              <div class="force-overflow">
                <div id="01001" class="titleOrange">Step 1</div>
                <h3>Select the Label Shape, Size & Material </h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01001.jpg" alt="..."> </a> To get started you need to select the template by using the  label filter. Open the label filter panel by clicking on <strong>Show Filter</strong> button. <br />
                  <br />
                  <a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01002.jpg" alt="..."> </a> You will need to first select the  <strong>Label  Category</strong>, <strong>Label Shape</strong> and <strong>Label Material </strong>and then by using the  slider controls, or free typing into the boxes, enter the width and height  dimensions to view the range of standard label sizes available within your  search criteria. <br />
                  <br />
                  <a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01003.jpg" alt="..."> </a> The label sizes will automatically appear on the page below  the filter and once you decide on a size for your label, then click on the blue <strong>Create Design</strong> button (on the right  of the page) for the label size and shape selected to start designing your  labels.<br />
                  <br />
                  You can also use the other filter options e.g. <strong>Label Finish</strong>, <strong>Label Colour,</strong> <strong>Label Adhesive</strong> and <strong>Printer/Copier Type</strong> to refine  your search.</p>
                <div id="01002" class="titleOrange m-t-20">Step 2</div>
                <h3>Select Your Design</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01004.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>On  this page you can either choose a design template, or begin with a blank  design. Select a category to review different designs from the left side panel  and the designs available for that category will be displayed for selection.  Alternatively you can begin with a blank template by clicking on the  <strong>Blank  Design</strong>&rdquo; button.</p>
                <h3 id="01003" >Create Design Screen</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01005.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>In this screen you can create designs using the tools  available and selecting objects from the left-hand panel, such as <strong>Images</strong>, <strong>Shapes</strong> and <strong>Text</strong> all of  which are editable through the customary functions of copy, cut, paste, delete,  undo and redo during the design process. </p>
                <h3 id="01004">Adding Images</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01007.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>At the top of the left-side panel is the <strong>Image</strong> button, which when opened, will  display a panel with category  options  and by opening a category you will be presented with a gallery from which you  can select images to use in your design, as outlined in the following section  of the guide.</p>
                <h3 id="01005">Gallery</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01008.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>In the gallery window you can select from the category list  on left-side and images will be displayed on the main panel from the category  selected. <br />
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01009.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                You can select from the images available, or add your own image by  clicking on the  <strong>Your Pictures</strong> tab, enabling you to upload images from your own file  storage, or if logged-in and have saved images in your account, use an image  from a previous design. <br />
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01010.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                By clicking on an image or saved file, it will be added  to the design screen canvas.
                </p>
                <h3 id="01006">Image</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01011.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>After adding an image on the design canvas you have a number  of different options. You can replace the image selected by clicking on it and  choosing a replacement image from the gallery. You can set an image as a  background, or use the crop tool to reduce some unwanted areas of the image, as  shown in the screen-shot seen above.</p>
                <h3 id="01007">Using Image Filters</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01012.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>You can use the different filters available to change the image colour, adjust the brightness, contrast, hue and colour saturation, by using the slider controls, or set the value in the box provided. </p>
                <h3 id="01008">Shape</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01013.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>The second tab down in the left-side panel, is for the selection of shapes. Click to open the panel and you will be presented with a drop-down list of categories, each category has different shape options that can be added to the design canvas.</p>
                <h3 id="01009">Working with Shapes</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01014.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>Once you have selected  the shape, use the features displayed in the shape panel to amend the shape for your design. You can alter  the line color and thickness, set the transparency and fill colour, using single colour, or combining colours with gradient effects. </p>
                <h3 id="01010">Text Box</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01015.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>The  third tab down from the top is to add text within your label design. By  clicking and opening this panel, you will be able to select and add text boxes  to the design canvas for editing, by clicking on the <strong>Add Text</strong> button. A Text box will appear on the center of the  canvas.</p>
                <h3 id="01011">Adding Text & Rounded Text</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01016.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>You can add plain and rounded text from the text panel by  clicking on the <strong>Add Text </strong>and <strong>Add Rounded Text</strong> buttons. You can  use  the text box to adjust width and  height, change colour font, pitch, style and transparency, or alter the text  direction and orientation , using a combination of the directional buttons and  the flip functions and rotational features found in the <strong>Tools </strong>tab.</p>
                <h3 id="01012">Tools </h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01017.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>The last tab is the tools feature in the left side panel,  providing  a range of options to amend  the images and text boxes included in your design, such as the  <strong>Arrange</strong>, <strong>Align</strong>, <strong>Rotate</strong> and <strong>Flip</strong> features. Using the <strong>Arrange</strong> feature  you can set the object order on the canvas, moving object to the front or back  of the design. With the <strong>Align</strong> function you can align the object to the canvas, or set the position to the  center of the canvas. Using the <strong>Rotate</strong> function will allow you to change and set the rotation of the object by using  the slider or you can add the value for custom rotation. While the <strong>Flip</strong> feature will allow you to  flip-over  the selected object  horizontally or vertically.<br />
                  <br />
                  <em>Please Note: A Simple Text box  cannot be "flipped" only a ronded text box.</em><br />
                </p>
                <h3 id="01013">Object List</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01018.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>As you select and use backgrounds, images, shapes and text  you will see a file reference appear in the <strong>Object List </strong>panel in the lower right corner of the design canvas.  You can select an individual item from the list by clicking on it for ease of  selection, or change the order by dragging an item selected up or down and you  can also lock the layer to prevent selection on canvas. </p>
                <p><br />
                  <br />
                  <!-- <em>Please Note: That a Simple Text box  cannot be flipped, only a ronded text box.</em><br />--> 
                </p>
                <h3 id="01014">Sheet Navigator</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01019.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>This feature directly above the Object List provides a  preview for the whole sheet of labels selected. There is the option to edit  labels collectively &ldquo;<strong>Edit All</strong>&rdquo; or  singularly &ldquo;<strong>Edit One</strong>&rdquo;<strong> </strong>if you want to produce different  designs on one sheet. You also have the option of re-sizing the Sheet Navigator  to improve the labels preview.</p>
                <div id="01015" class="titleOrange m-t-20">Step 3</div>
                <h3>Preview Sheet</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01020.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>When you have completed your label design  click on the   &ldquo;<strong>Preview &amp; Print</strong>&rdquo; button  located in the top right-hand corner and you will navigate to the &ldquo;<strong>Preview Sheet</strong>&rdquo; where you can view your  completed sheet and use the magnifier feature if required. </p>
                <h3 id="01020">Digitally Printed Labels (200 DPI)</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01021.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>Once you are satisfied that your design is complete there  are 3 options to produce finished labels. The first is for AA Labels to produce  printed labels for you and on the right-hand side of the panel ,at the top  there is a button for <strong>Digitally Printed  Labels </strong>you can enter the number of sheets required to calculate the price  and <strong>Add To Basket </strong>to place an order  for high resolution (200DPI) digitally printed labels.</p>
                <h3 id="01016">Plain Labels (100 DPI)</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01022.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>The second option and middle button <strong>Buy Plain Labels</strong>, click on &ldquo;<strong>Click  Here</strong>&rdquo; button to open the panel. You can calculate the price for plain  labels for the label materials selected and place an order for plain sheets on  which to print your design&rsquo;s. Upon order confirmation you will be able to  download your saved PDF file at an image resolution of 100DPI. </p>
                <h3 id="01017">Download Free PDF (72 DPI)</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01023.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>The third option is to download and print your label design  for free. You can download your design in PDF format by clicking on the &ldquo;<strong>Click Here</strong>&rdquo; button for printing on your  existing label sheets, without having to place a new order.</p>
                <h3 id="01018">Apply Design To Another Product</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01024.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <br />
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01026.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>At the bottom of the panel on the right-hand side of the  page, there is the option of applying your design to another shape and size of  label, with closely related options displayed, but you can browse all available  labels by clicking on the <strong>View More </strong>button,  which will open the <strong>Label Finder </strong>filter.</p>
                <h3 id="01030">Back to Canvas</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01030.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>At  any point you can save your design to your account and project for future use  and reference by clicking on the <strong>Save</strong> button and your design will be filed.<br />
                </p>
                <h3 id="01019">Save</h3>
                <p><a href="#" class="thumbnail" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#lightbox"> <img onerror='imgError(this);' src="<?=Assets?>images/help/01027.jpg" alt="..."> </a></p>
                <p>At  any point you can save your design to your account and project for future use  and reference by clicking on the <strong>Save</strong> button and your design will be filed.<br />
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
